&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Landscaping
&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Notwithstanding
     the details submitted with the application, no above grounds works shall
     take place until the following hard and soft landscape details have been
     submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-top:0cm&quot; start=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;a&quot;&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Planting plans and full planting specification for the
     whole scheme including details of the number of all trees, hedges and
     shrubs to be planted, together with a planting schedule providing sizes
     and total quantities of individual species. The number, type and location
     of trees should reflect that agreed under condition 2 (approved plans).
     These plans should also show appropriate plant species given likely levels
     of shade or direct sunlight. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Details of tree planting within hard landscaped areas
     to include root cell crates; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Street furniture, including general waste and recycling
     bins, benches and any other relevant items;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Details of boundaries including materials, plans images
     of walls, fencing, gates and railings; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Details of lighting (in relation to appearance/design);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Details of wayfinding signage/public art; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Details of surfacing materials to be used in the
     external finishes of all roads, footpaths, and parking areas, together
     with specification of edging and kerbs; and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
     &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Landscape, ecology and habitat management plan.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;The development
shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;










The approved landscaping schemes shall be
implemented during the first planting season following the completion of the
relevant area of the development and shall thereafter be maintained for a
period of five years. Any trees, shrubs or grassed areas which dies, are
diseased or vandalised within this period shall be replaced within the first
available planting season.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;TFL Infrastructure Protection (3)
&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;



 Before the
     super-structure construction stage begins, no works shall be carried out
     until the following, in consultation with TfL Infrastructure Protection,
     have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning
     authority:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol start=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;a&quot;&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Provide details on the use of tall plant/scaffolding and lifting equipment, if any.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Provide temporary works and permanent works design and construction details/methodology for all structures.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;TFL Infrastructure Protection (2)
&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;



 Before the sub-structure
     construction stage begins, no works shall be carried out until the
     following, in consultation with TfL Infrastructure Protection, have been
     submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol start=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;a&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;Provide details of foundations, basement and ground floor structures, or any other structures below ground level, including piling (temporary and permanent)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;No glare or glint to be shed onto the railway from the construction, the completed structure, or any lighting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;
 
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Tree Protection
&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;



 The development hereby
     approved shall be constructed in accordance with the details set out in
     the Arboricultural Method Statement, included within the approved
     Arboricultural Impact Assessment prepared by A.T. Coombes Associated Ltd.
     unless otherwise approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;BREEAM
&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;



 Notwithstanding the
     details submitted with the application, the development shall not be
     occupied until a post-construction assessment demonstrating how the entire
     development will achieve BREEAM Excellent has been submitted to and
     approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Cycle Parking and Bin Storage
&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;



 The cycle parking and
     bin store facilities as shown on the hereby approved Proposed Site Layout
     Plan (BCH-LD-XX-00-DR-A-000020, P02) shall be constructed, furnished and
     made available for use prior to first occupation/ use of any part of the
     development hereby approved. These cycle parking and bin storage areas shall
     thereafter be maintained and kept available for use by staff and visitors
     at all times.&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;TFL Infrastructure Protection (1)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

 Before the
     pre-commencement/site formation/demolition stage begins, no works shall be
     carried out until the following, in consultation with TfL Infrastructure
     Protection, have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local
     planning authority:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-top:0cm&quot; start=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;a&quot;&gt;
 &lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt;&quot;&gt;Provide details for demolition&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt;&quot;&gt;Mitigate the effects of noise and vibration arising from the adjoining operations within the railway structures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt;&quot;&gt;No claims to be made against TfL or London Underground by the property owners, tenants, occupants or lessees of the property for any noise or vibration resulting from London Underground running, operating and maintaining the adjacent railway.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt;&quot;&gt;Demonstrate that any EMC emissions from any plant or equipment to be used on the site or in the finished structure will not adversely affect LU equipment or signalling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-top:0cm&quot; start=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;a&quot;&gt;
 &lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-top:0cm&quot; start=&quot;10&quot; type=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
